<TITLE> Bodies of 4 Bangladeshi workers return from Saudi Arabia Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 03 (bdnews24.com)The bodies of four Bangladeshis among the 11 killed in a road accident in Saudi Arabia on Jan 31, will be brought back to Dhaka Tuesday morning, 32 days after the accident. Earlier, the officials of the Bangladesh mission in Saudi Arabia had told the media that the corpses would be sent to Dhaka seven days after the accident. Foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury will receive the bodies at the airport and hand them over to family members, the foreign ministry's public relations officer Yeakub Ali told bdnews24.com. "We have managed clearance from the Saudi government to get the four bodies back. The remaining bodies will be sent back to Bangladesh soon," Mizanur Rahman, an official of the Bangladesh embassy in Saudi Arabia, told bdnews24.com from Riyadh Monday. He said that the embassy could not get sponsors in Saudi Arabia to send the bodies back. The workers were killed while returning from their workplace in the Saudi central province of Dammam. The bodies were kept in a mortuary in Saudi Arabia. bdn
